=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   And now, the bad points. </span><hr size=1> OK as promised, I also point out the bad points of the game.  IMHO they should have delayed release of this game for another 1 or 2 months.  But corporate decisions being what they are.... it's too late to stop them.<br>
<br>
<br>
1) game is still not very stable, but that's the least of my worries. game stability is always something they try to fix and improve with every patch <br>
<br>
2) a few primary classes are BROKEN!!  they are gonna release the game knowing that important base classes like the medic (i.e. the healer class) is totally screwed up<br>
<br>
This is kinda like releasing a final version of Everquest II and then hearing that the cleric class is broken because their heal spells don't work well, and the reason they dont work is because all clerical heal spells require a rare gem component that can only be foraged by wood elves. Yeah this sounds stupid?  Well, that's exactly how screwed up the healer class (medics/doctors) is in SWG right now.  One week prior to retail release.<br>
<br>
Jaranna also noted that at least a couple of classes have not even been tested fully.  Ugh.  <br>
<br>
<br>
3)  Game physics is lame.  I mean lame-O lame.  That's Lame with a capital L. <br>
<br>
****  characters do not suffer damage from jumping extreme vertical heights.  WTF!!!  this means that if your SWG character jumps down a 2 story building, he will never suffer a single point of body injury.  This is a screwed up system.<br>
<br>
****  The JUMP feature does almost nothing.  There is like a 2 or 3 second enforced delay time from the moment you PRESS the &quot;jump&quot; key on your keyboard to the time you actually see your character leap up into the air.  Absolutely lame.  <br>
<br>
**** Characters do not really &quot;swim&quot;.  They just wade across bodies of  water.  Characters can never drown.  Characters can never sink underwater.  They are not even allowed to submerge their heads under the waterline.  They just enter the water and they are automagically dog paddling all the time.  Hence, bodies of water are merely 2-dimensional terrain.  They are not 3-dimensional terrain because you can never submerge or sink underwater.  This is lame lame physics. <br>
<br>
<br>
4) SWG game controls (keyboard and mousing) are disorienting.  Yeah, you eventually get used to them.  But still, they are very unintuitive compared to any other MMORPG.  Even the default keyboard commands on Everquest are 50 times more sensible. <br>
<br>
<br>
bah... I need a break, I cant continue.... too much to write LOL<br>
<br>
